bio:
I am a qualified and experienced analytics manager with over nine years of experience in working on projects across multiple sectors, geographies and demands. I specialize in R , SAS and Analytics


While I have spent the past year working with and picking some courses with the Statistics Department of University of Tennessee, Knoxville, I have been educated with a Post Graduate Diploma in Management from the Indian Institute of Management, Lucknow.  I also have a bachelors degree in mechanical engineering from the Delhi College of Engineering. I believe my extensive education helped me with sharpening my analytical skills as well as give me confidence to handle complex tools and presenting the results and delivery to a wide sector of global clients.

Having worked with dealer management inventory and optimization for both Indian and American automakers, I have also worked on projects with financial services marketing for cross selling portfolio products to retail consumers across the globe. I started work with analytics more than seven years ago while it was still a nascent sector and profession within India. Based on my track record, I moved rapidly from my basic training at General Electric to help startup and ISO certify the Gurgaon Analytics practise of WNS prior to its initial public offering. Working with Citigroup’s India retail operations helped me develop actionable insights in actual executing of data analytics across the demand chain.

My most recent role had been a consultant for my own firm Decisionstats.com in which I handled clients ranging from a prominent French software company, a global entertainment starting up in India, web analytics and content generation for online media and supply chain optimization for a large manufacturing setup across North America. During this process I used and trained extensively in analytical tools like JMP, SAS, SPSS, R, KXEN, and helped execute the results in consultation with various stake holders across levels of management. I was invited to the Data Mining 2009 conference in Las Vegas as a guest of SAS Institute, the world’s biggest analytics company and to the Big Data Summit in New York on behalf of Aster Data.

Overall, I have worked and interacted with some of the best users as well as practitioners of analytics in the world and I hope to continue the journey with continuing results.

# Capabilities
* Programming in C, C++, Java, Python, and assembly language for ARM, Power, ColdFire, and X86 processors running Linux (embedded, desktop, and server) and real-time operating systems.
* Implementing wired and wireless networking protocols and audio/video codecs.
* Writing requirements documents, system specifications, and standards.
* Architecting complex systems, software, and systems-on-a-chip (SoCs).

# Work Experience
## 2008–present [Petroleum Geo-Services](http://www.pgs.com), Austin, TX – Staff Engineer
* Designing and implementing embedded, client, and server software for a complex fiber optic seismic data acquisition system. The embedded subsystem is implemented in C, C++, and assembly language on Analog Devices SHARC DSPs and TI OMAP-L137 processors, the latter running Linux. The control and monitoring subsystem is browser-based, with the server components implemented in C++ and Python using Linux, Apache, Django, and PostgreSQL; the client subsystem is implemented in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The embedded and server subsystems communicate using JSON over ZeroMQ; the client and server subsystems communicate using JSON over RESTful HTTP.
* Wrote embedded real-time seismic data acquisition software in C and assembler using SDCC and FreeRTOS for a system based on Cirrus Logic’s geophysical chipset and an 8051 processor.

## 2000–2008 [Motorola/Freescale Semiconductor](http://www.freescale.com), Austin, TX

### Corporate Solutions and Software Team – Senior Member of the Technical Staff
* Wrote C, C++, and shell script code for industrial market system solutions based on ARM, Power, and ColdFire processors, spanning everything from SoC initialization to Linux graphics device drivers to application framework porting.
* Responsible for coordinating Freescale’s participation in several standards development organizations.
* Wrote the network and transport sections of the draft ISA100.11a industrial wireless sensor network standard, which are based on IETF RFC4944 (Internet Protocol v6 over IEEE 802.15.4).
* Authored a draft standard for controlling consumer electronics devices based on IEEE 802.15.4 wireless personal area network (WPAN) technology, which evolved into the ZigBee R4CE standard.

### Networking and Computing Systems Group – Systems Engineer/Technical Marketer
* Architected SoCs that included Power architecture processor cores, communications accelerators (PowerQUICC), 10/100/1000Mbps Ethernet, PCI, PCI Express, USB, and encryption accelerators.
* Located SoC IP blocks inside and outside of Freescale, evaluated outside IP blocks, and negotiated IP licensing contracts.
* Researched markets, identified target customers, analyzed supply and value chains, created competitive analyses, wrote market and product requirements documents, and calculated financial returns.
* Represented Freescale in the IEEE 802.11 working group and the Wi-Fi Alliance.

### Transportation and Standard Products Group – Systems and Software Engineer
* Architected SoCs and systems that included ColdFire and ARM processor cores, 10/100Mbps Ethernet, IEEE 802.11, UWB, USB, audio/video codecs, digital rights management, and encryption accelerators.
* Created systems requirements documents, modeled system performance, performed architectural trade-off analyses, identified and mitigated project risks, and wrote system and SoC specifications.
* Worked with offshore IDHs and ODMs to create hardware and software reference designs; responsibilities included evaluating, selecting, and managing vendors, writing requirements and specification documents, negotiating contracts, designing software APIs, and reviewing deliverables.
* Developed Linux device drivers and libraries in C for audio/video playback and networking.
* Represented Motorola in the IEEE 802.15 working group, edited the Bluetooth Basic Imaging Profile standard, and contributed to the Bluetooth Basic Printing Profile standard.

## 1999–2000 MSHOW.com, Austin, TX – A/V Development Lead
* Managed a software development team that designed, developed, and deployed an audio/video encoding and streaming system based on RealNetworks and Microsoft Windows Media technologies.
* Invented and implemented a client-side method for synchronizing multimedia events to RealNetworks and Windows Media streams to compensate for network buffering and latency.	
* Designed and implemented a server in Java that controlled operator-less audio conference bridges and integrated them with other web conferencing components.

## 1997–1999 [Cirrus Logic](http://www.cirrus.com), Austin, TX
